runs.comm: down the leg side
oh well bowled - that takes the splice of the bat, the ball flying safely short of third man
fast and straight, and a hint of swing - but no more than a hint. Flipped off his pads
fullish, he's forward and defending to point who wings in an intimidatory throw
goes for a pull, yes, this'll be easily taken - he's skied it straight to the skyscraping figure of Broad at mid-on
oh that's out. No it's not - rapped on the pads but a little too high
outside off, left alone
what a cracker that is! Cuts back on the right hander at pace. That moved some, I'm here to tell you
flays the bat at it - that's the spirit! Whack it! - and it flies down to third man
catch that, catch it - catch it in the crowd! He goes for a pull and it sails over midwicket. A monstrous hit!
steps to leg and tries to slap it over midwicket
spearing into his legs, he flicks to leg
beautiful! Nothing more than a little flick off his toes and it absolutely sped for four. Great timing.
ooh that's more like it from the man they call James Anderson. An inswinger which nearly knocks the hefty figure of Reekers off his feet
six more, please! What a stroke that is from Reekers - a short-arm jab and it sails flat for six.
gives himself room and guides it out to the off side
Reekers goes for another leg-side glory flip but is squared up
youch, that spat up from nowhere and hammered into his gloves. Good pace from Anderson
short of a length, bashed out to the off side
quite wide of the off stump, Reekers steps outside leg - almost off the cut strip
got him! Reekers is furious with himself as he attempts another pull but can't time it
short, wide and cut hard to third man
that's a cracker to start his innings. A jabby cut and he's timed it perfectly past point for four. Broad's furious. But then, Broad's always furious.
slammed to mid-off
off the pad and down to fine leg
quick ball on his legs, and again it's off the pads to the leg side
too quick to handle, and an excellent line on middle-and-leg
beaten for pace! And lift, too. That shot off the surface!
guided down to third man
a waste from Sidebottom - down the leg side, and not even Foster can stop it
shot - that's a superb pull stroke in front of square for four. Really classy
slower ball, cuts back into him
good, straight and slower delivery on middle stump which is carefully and studiously defended
more runs for Netherlands, albeit via an inauspicious inside edge past the stumps
dropped to leg for a hasty single
shot - a golf-swing-style club down the ground for six. 83 metres of Netherlands glory
on middle-and-leg - good line with which to start - whipped to leg
reverse sweep - has he got hold of it? You bet he has - he's timed it over point for four!
holds this one back does Rashid, and it's defended
ooh a quicker ball, the slider I reckon, and it passes the outside edge. Great take from Foster
stands tall and fairly thwacks it out to extra cover
the googly is stroked to mid-on who is quite deep, and a little lazy - they pick up two. Top work from Netherlands
full, driven hard out to deep extra cover
full toss, he opens the face and cracks it out to the off side
thin inside edge! That could so easily have smashed his stumps apart. Good effort by Foster diving to his left
hooked out to deep square leg
uppercut down to third man - Shah has to run a good 10 yards and prevents four
well a rare dot ball this time, worked to midwicket

got him! Rashid's first international wicket and a good one it is, too, beating the right-hander in the flight with a classical legbreak, and Foster takes it high to his right before whipping off the bails
well that's one way to start your innings! He plants his foot and absolutely murders this in front of square over midwicket! Take that
flicked to leg for a single. Excellent, urgent cricket from Netherlands
cut hard past point - has it got the legs for four? Not quite, but they do get three
swept around the corner
another superb slog-sweep for four, timing it sweetly! That absolutely flew off his bat
short of a length and nudged off his hip
full toss outside off, steps to leg and flings his bat at it, the ball flying over Rashid at backward point. Four more!
dropped to leg - he's placed that really well, too! They'll get an easy two
another single stolen to the leg side
a wide down the leg side - attempted bouncer? Well, either way, it was misdirected
a quicker delivery which brushes off his pads, or perhaps shirt, but again the strike's rotated
shimmies down the pitch and smudges one to long-on for another two
on middle stump, driven to mid-on
guided past the diving point - slight mixup between this pair! One of them didn't realise the ball had escaped the fielder
goes for a slog sweep but can't make contact, the ball rebounding off Foster's gloves
a slow, loopy full toss. de Grooth takes a step down the pitch and flings it powerfully over midwicket - excellent placement, and a shoddy ball from Collingwood
he plays and misses outside off. Good take from Foster
outside off, another dibbly dobbler which is whipped to square leg
a full toss driven powerfully straight to the sweeper on the deep extra cover boundary
wellied around the corner - mistimed; his bottom hand came off the bat
tries to whack it over Sidebottom but the bowler fields it comfortably. And then attempts to wang it back at his head. Aggression - or, rather, nerves - from Sidebottom
driven out to cover for a quick single
timed that very well, too, lifting it with great audacity and chutzpah over midwicket. Pietersen would've been proud of that
driven to long-on
half a shout as he's rapped on the pads, down the leg side - but they pick up two! Really, Sidebottom should have kept it down to one there. Poor stuff from England
plays and misses. Had he connected, that was heading onto the Bakerloo Line
flicked to leg for a single - but they're coming back for a second. In comes the throw but Bopara mucks it up quite spectacularly. Wheels. Coming. Off
that's not six. That's twelve! A superb pull for six, miles and miles into the stands! What timing
flicked to leg
oh he's got him now, ending a wonderfully entertaining knock. Tries to work it to leg, but he's squared up and it's safely held by Key at mid-off
angled across the right-hander who plays and misses
sliced down to third man who makes a good stop. The first run is made comfortably - a bit of a slip on the second, though, and suddenly it's all rather hectic and calamitous!
square-drives this full toss out to the off side
fuller delivery on middle-and-leg, nudged to mid-on
ooh and it's wided. Boos around the ground, but I think that's fair enough
another wideish delivery, very full too, and he plays and misses
steps out to the off side and flips this to short fine leg. Picks him out perfectly!
a prodigiously spinning leggie beats the batsman's hopeful swipe
slog-swept for a single - timed it too well, really
comes down the pitch and blocks it with his pad to the leg side
he's nailed this. He's only nailed it! Short and wide from Rashid, he sat back and cut it with tremendous power for four
good comeback by Rashid, flighting this on leg stump and giving it a big rip
a scything swipe to deep midwicket
driven out to mid-off who makes a brilliant stop. A mix-up between the batsmen - he'll be run out here if the throw's accurate. No! It's a shocker into Foster from Collingwood
outside off, he whips it to deep square leg
chopped to Key at point - and they get a single with remarkable ease. England ... wake up
better delivery - fast and swinging back into the right hander
slammed to cover
oops - he goes for a pull but skies it. Huge pressure on Shah ... who holds a fine catch and roars his delight! That ought to improve England's standing as far as Duckworth-Lewis figures go
excellent length by Rashid - well bowled. Defended
slammed to long-off
uppercut past point - Key and Broad give chase, and Key slides like a teenager down a grassy bank. Has he saved it though? It's desperately tight, this. And he has! Great work
he goes inside out and throws his bat at it - a thumping, crunching, glorious extra cover drive for four! What tenacity. That could be the game!
skips down the pitch and whacks it to mid-on
comes down the pitch but Rashid spots him, fires it into his legs
bang! More outstanding timing - standing outside off and hammering it, but straight to deep extra cover
worked to leg
down the pitch and he whacks it to leg
a fast delivery down the leg side, which he flicks to leg
ah, well bowled - a slower ball yorker outside the off stump

got him! Wright's taken a superb catch at deep extra cover, and only just! Stepped outside leg, tried to clear the boundary but Wright was there - and the ball squeezed into the nook of his lower and upper arm! Serious piece of fortune for England
driven hard to mid-off - short mid-off, in fact. Good thinking by England
off his legs - short midwicket has all three stumps to aim at. And misses! They so rarely hit the stums, England - it's remarkable
full toss, slices this powerfully over extra cover - Morgan flies like Superman but drops it while airborne, parrying it over the rope! Four more to Netherlands!
drives inside out, over mid-off to long-off - just a single
rapped on the pads, the ball somehow finds its way to third man. Two more for Netherlands. Everything's going their way
a waist-high full toss, slapped with tennis-style boshing past cover
cracked out to the off side, Broad fields and should run him out - but misses! That's the fourth run-out opportunity they've missed tonight alone

tries to smack it out to cover but can't time it. Broad fields and does a Jonty Rhodes, diving onto the stumps. But as his right hand (holding the ball) hits the turf, he releases the ball - it's his hand which smashes the bails! Not out
Broad's dropped a wellied smash to a full toss! High above his head and it took a while to reach him
he plays and misses, the ball flies through to keeper who is standing back - and they run a bye!
another smash, but he picks out mid-on! Only a single. Good grief, this is so tense

goes for a club, Broad again fields - they run, and Broad has all three stumps as he collects it in his follow through. But he misses, and they run an overthrow. They're through and Netherlands have scored a brilliantly, outstanding upset here for the first match at Lord's!
